column5: Just wondering if anybody's fished that way recently and if they sell minnows that way??? thanks in advance......
Yup just got back an hour ago. Landed one pike, and lost 2. All on my new tip up I picked up yesterday at the show. And yes they do sell minnows.
Pidge, how big was the one you got?
Never had a tape, but I'd honestly say about 20 inches long. All the pike I have ever pulled out of that lake were all around that size. I'v never herd of any one pulling one out much bigger.
thanks for info.might have to drill some holes tomorrow,fish it in the summer,incredible fishery, a couple of pics from last summer

hELLO  MY WIFE AND I LOVE TO FISH THERE AS WELL..    WE ALWAYS CATCH PIKE AND PERCH WHEN WE GO..   NEVER SEEN OR HEARD OF ANY WALLEYS CAUGHT BUT HAVE CAUGHT CRAPPIE AND TONS OF BASS..  GREAT FAMILY EVENT PLACE..  dAVE
wow Merc. thats a nice bass outa that lake, pike look like what I usually catch size wise. I'm with Dmasse, pretty sure there is no walleye in the lake
